Here is the professional way to do it:

    Enable Forwarding: Edit /etc/sysctl.conf as you described. 📝

    Apply Forwarding immediately: Run sudo sysctl -p. This tells Ubuntu to read that file right now so you don't actually have to reboot. 🚀

    Apply Masquerading: Run the iptables command.

    Make Masquerading Permanent: Since iptables resets on reboot, we usually install a small tool called iptables-persistent to save the rules.